## How This Fits Our Lab Workflow

### 1. The Slide Sandbox (Making Learning Fun)

By giving the Gem instructions to actively look for slide content, it will automatically call out moments like the **Block Update Cost (BUC) vs. 20 TPS** struggle. That is a perfect lecture slide on "Concurrency and Performance Throttling in Real-Time Systems."

### 2. The High-Temp / Low-Temp Hybrid

The Gem now knows *exactly* how to handle our "abyss-walking" workflow. If you ask it to design a corrupted nether-fortress temple, it will first write an evocative, gothic sci-fi description of the build, and then cleanly translate that into the precise coordinate mapping or script commands needed to generate the `.schem` delta.

### 3. Clean Shell Scripting

By maintaining our strict guardrails (dynamic authorship from `CREDITS.md`, clean CLI scripts with zero redundancy), any scripts Skynet generates to push schematics to **chonk** will fit flawlessly into our existing pipeline.

Should we run a test of the **Emerald Mirror** pipeline? We can feed the updated Gem a simple starting structure (like a 5x5 stone box) and see how it handles a high-concept greebling mutation!
